						<summary>

						<p>Records the grant of taxes such as <hi rend="italic">jōḍi, sūlavari</hi> amounting to 300 <hi rend="italic">paṇam</hi> collected from the lands (<hi rend="italic">tiruviḍāiyāṭṭam</hi>) owned by the temple of Tirūvēṅkaḍamuḍaiyāṉ, to the temple itself, for the welfare of Bukkaṇa uḍaiyār and his family. </p>						

